article.headline: UALR 58, Troy 56
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Will Neighbour had 14 points and 11 rebounds Thursday night and UALR defeated Troy 58-56 in the Sun Belt Conference opener for both schools. Leroy Isler had 12 points and nine rebounds, Taggart Lockhart had 11 points and James White scored 10 for UALR (5-3) Hunter Williams had 11 points and seven assists for Troy (4-4). Williams' 3-pointer with 10.7 seconds left got Troy within 57-56. Josh Hagins made one of two free throws for UALR, giving Troy a chance to tie or win, but the last shot fell short. Emil Jones scored 10 points and Ray Chambers had eight points and 11 rebounds for Troy, which led 33-28 at halftime. UALR was 14 of 22 from the free-throw line. Troy was 2 for 2, both by Justin Wright in the first half.
